In [3]:
(x_train, y_train), (x_test, y_test) = tf.keras.datasets.cifar10.load_data()
assert x_train.shape == (50000, 32, 32, 3)
assert x_test.shape == (10000, 32, 32, 3)
assert y_train.shape == (50000, 1)
assert y_test.shape == (10000, 1)

x_train = (x_train-127.5)/(127.5)
x_test = (x_test-127.5)/(127.5)

y_train = to_categorical(y_train, 10)
y_test = to_categorical(y_test, 10)

In [8]:
x_train_c1 = np.array([np.flipud(x) for x in x_train[:-500]])
y_train_c1 = np.ones(shape=x_train_c1.shape[0]).reshape(x_train_c1.shape[0],1)
y_train_c1 = y_train_c1.astype('int')

print('train.shape        test.shape:')
print(x_train_c1.shape, y_train_c1.shape)

train.shape        test.shape:
(49500, 32, 32, 3) (49500, 1)
In [9]:
x_train_c2 = np.array([np.rot90(x) for x in x_train[:-500]])
y_train_c2 = np.ones(shape=x_train_c2.shape[0]).reshape(x_train_c2.shape[0],1)
y_train_c2 = y_train_c2*2
y_train_c2 = y_train_c2.astype('int')
print('train.shape        test.shape:')
print(x_train_c2.shape, y_train_c2.shape)

train.shape        test.shape:
(49500, 32, 32, 3) (49500, 1)

x_train_pretext = np.concatenate((x_train_c0, x_train_c1), axis=0)
x_train_pretext = np.concatenate((x_train_pretext, x_train_c2), axis=0)
del x_train_c0
del x_train_c1
del x_train_c2

y_train_pretext = np.concatenate((y_train_c0, y_train_c1), axis=0)
y_train_pretext = np.concatenate((y_train_pretext, y_train_c2), axis=0)
del y_train_c0
del y_train_c1

In [12]:
# pretext model

model_pretext = keras.Sequential([

#                 Input(shape=(32,32,3)),
                Conv2D(10, kernel_size=(5,5), kernel_initializer=HeNormal(), activation='relu', strides=1,
                       name='layer1_conv2d', input_shape=(32,32,3)),
                MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2), strides=2, name='layer1_maxpool2d'),
                
                Conv2D(10, kernel_size=(5,5), kernel_initializer=HeNormal(), activation='relu', strides=1,
                       name='layer2_conv2d'),
                MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2), strides=2, name='layer2_maxpool2d'),

                Flatten(name='flatten'),

                Dense(20, activation='relu', kernel_initializer=HeNormal(), name='layer3_dense'),
                Dense(3, activation='softmax', kernel_initializer=HeNormal(), name='output')
                
                           
])

model_pretext.compile(
    optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=0.001),
    loss = losses.SparseCategoricalCrossentropy(),
    metrics=['Accuracy']
)

model_pretext.summary()

In [8]:
model_transfer = keras.Sequential(
    [Input(shape=(32,32,3)) ]+
    model_transfer_base.layers[:-1])

# model_transfer.add(Dense(512, activation='relu', kernel_initializer=HeUniform()))

model_transfer.add(Dense(10, activation='softmax', kernel_initializer=HeUniform()))

optimizers_layers = []
for i in [0,2,5]:
    optimizers_layers.append((Adam(learning_rate=1e-6), model_transfer.layers[i]))
optimizers_layers.append((Adam(learning_rate=1e-3), model_transfer.layers[6]))  

model_transfer.compile(
    optimizer=tfa.optimizers.MultiOptimizer(optimizers_layers),
#     optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=0.001),
#     loss = losses.SparseCategoricalCrossentropy(),
    loss = 'categorical_crossentropy',
    metrics=['Accuracy']
)

model_transfer.summary()

transfer_hist = pd.DataFrame(model_transfer_fit.history['Accuracy'], columns=['Accuracy'])
transfer_hist['loss'] =  model_transfer_fit.history['loss']
transfer_hist['val_loss'] =  model_transfer_fit.history['val_loss'] + [np.NAN]*9900
transfer_hist['val_Accuracy'] =  model_transfer_fit.history['val_Accuracy'] + [np.NAN]*9900

transfer_hist.to_csv('transfer_hist.csv')

In [7]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
fig, ax=plt.subplots(1,1,figsize=(10,7))
sns.lineplot(x =baseline_hist.epoch*100, y=transfer_hist['val_Accuracy'], label="Transfer Learning Model")
sns.lineplot(x =baseline_hist.epoch*100,y=baseline_hist['val_Accuracy'], label="Baseline Model")
plt.legend()
plt.title("HW3:P2 Comparision betweeen Validation accuracy of Baseline & Transfer Learning Model ")

plt.show()
